The paper deals with the optimization of a scenario involving robots and dedicated agents, which falls under the scope of robotics (cs.RO). The use of objective functions and computational methods to find the optimal schedule suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.MA). The concept of persistent autonomy and the need for resource management implies a systems and control (cs.SY) perspective. Finally, the use of optimization techniques and computational study suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG).
